  "notes": "Captures a disposable-customer store-credit flow. The recorder uses storeCreditAccountCredit with the customer id to make Shopify create a real store credit account, captures account-ID validation branches and owner-ID validation branches, then replays account-ID credit/debit mutations plus downstream direct/nested balance reads. The 2026-04 refresh additionally records creditInput.notify acceptance, public-schema attribution rejection, debitInput unsupported notify/attribution rejection, debitInput unsupported currency asymmetry, debitInput zero/negative amount wording, ACCOUNT_NOT_FOUND precedence over zero amount for missing credit/debit account IDs, EXPIRES_AT_IN_PAST precedence over negative credit amount for an existing account, CREDIT_LIMIT_EXCEEDED for credits at/above Shopify's captured account limit, a CHF owner-id credit success branch outside the old local allow-list, and result-only USDC/XXX credit inputs returning top-level CURRENCY_CODE_INVALID errors. Expected differences are limited to live Shopify IDs versus proxy-local synthetic IDs for locally created customers/accounts and GraphQL location offsets for validation replay documents."
}
